## How to Run the Project

Follow these steps to run the face mask detection system on your local machine.

---

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd Face-Mask-Detection
```

---

### 2. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

Activate it:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

### 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

If needed, install additional packages:

```bash
pip install tensorflow opencv-python numpy imutils scipy
```

---

### 4. Run Image Mask Detection

To detect mask from a single image:

```bash
python image_mask_detector.py --image images/example.jpg
```

📌 Replace `example.jpg` with your own image path.

---

### 5. Run Live Mask Detection (Webcam)

To start real-time detection using webcam:

```bash
python live_mask_detector.py
```

📌 Make sure your webcam is connected.

---

### 6. Output

* Detected faces will be highlighted with bounding boxes
* Labels will show:

  * Mask (Green)
  * No Mask (Red)
* Confidence score will also be displayed

---

### Notes

* Ensure all model files are present:

  * `face_detector/`
  * `my_mask_model.h5`
* If webcam doesn’t open, check camera permissions
* Use proper Python version (recommended: 3.8–3.10)

---
